Name: Notes
Arrests:
Rates refer to the number of felonies reported per 1,000 residents. U.S. Census Bureau 2000 Decennial Census counts were used to calculate rates for years 2000 through 2004. See Total Population data for more detailed notes and sources for population data. Information is accurate as of the date it was queried from the system of record, but should be considered a close approximation of current records, due to complaint revisions and updates. 

Precinct and boroughwide totals might not sum to the citywide total, as they include arrests occurring within the Department of Corrections.
